# Anuvaad v2.0 — Premium SaaS Transformation

## Full Product Audit Results

### Current Architecture
| Layer | Technology | Status |
|---|---|---|
| Frontend | Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS + ES Modules | ❌ No framework, no component system |
| Backend | FastAPI (Python) | ✅ Solid, well-structured |
| Auth | Supabase (email + Google OAuth) | ⚠️ Works but basic |
| Billing | Stripe checkout + webhooks → Supabase | ⚠️ Checkout only, no billing portal |
| Editor | CodeMirror 6 via esm.sh import maps | ⚠️ Works but brittle CDN dependency |
| Deploy | Docker + Nginx + docker-compose | ✅ Good |
| Tests | 50 pytest tests | ✅ Good backend coverage |
| PWA | manifest.json + service worker | ⚠️ Basic |
| SEO | Meta tags + OG + sitemap | ⚠️ No landing page, no content pages |

### Critical Issues Found

| Issue | Severity | Details |
|---|---|---|
| No landing page | 🔴 Critical | App goes straight to editor — zero conversion |
| No component system | 🔴 Critical | 2489-line CSS, 315-line HTML monolith |
| No dashboard | 🔴 Critical | No logged-in experience, no workspace |
| No TypeScript | 🟠 High | 10 JS modules with no type safety |
| CDN-dependent editor | 🟠 High | esm.sh imports break if CDN is down |
| 69KB CSS monolith | 🟠 High | Not tree-shakeable, not modular |
| No billing portal | 🟠 High | Users can't manage subscriptions |
| No team/collab features | 🟡 Medium | No multi-user, no sharing |
| No analytics | 🟡 Medium | Zero visibility into user behavior |
| No error monitoring | 🟡 Medium | No Sentry, no alerting |

