## Transformation Strategy

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Key Decision: Preserve the FastAPI backend as-is.** It's well-tested (50 tests), well-structured, and handles all API logic correctly. The transformation is a **frontend rebuild** from vanilla HTML/JS to Next.js, while the Python backend remains the API server.

### Architecture After Transformation

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Next.js 14 (App Router)                    │
│  ├── Landing page (SSR, SEO)                │
│  ├── Auth pages (Supabase)                  │
│  ├── Dashboard (client-side)                │
│  ├── Translator workspace                   │
│  ├── Billing (Stripe portal)                │
│  └── Legal + SEO pages                      │
└─────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘
              │ API calls
┌─────────────▼───────────────────────────────┐
│  FastAPI Backend (unchanged)                │
│  ├── /api/code-to-english                   │
│  ├── /api/generate-from-english             │
│  ├── /api/english-to-code                   │
│  ├── /api/code-to-code                      │
│  ├── /api/subscription-status               │
│  ├── /api/webhook/stripe                    │
│  └── /api/health                            │
└─────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘
              │
┌─────────────▼───────────────────────────────┐
│  Supabase (Auth + DB)                       │
│  ├── user auth (email, Google, GitHub)       │
│  └── user_subscriptions table               │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

